-- European Stocks Resume Gains, Led by Repsol, Galp, BG on Brazil Investment
-- B y   D a v i d   M e r r i t t
-- 2010-10-01T07:57:23Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-01/european-stocks-resume-gains-led-by-repsol-galp-bg-on-brazil-investment.html
European stocks resumed their
advance, led by a rally oil and gas shares as China’s Sinopec
pledged to invest $7.1 billion in Repsol YPF SA’s Brazilian
unit. U.S. futures and Asian shares rose.  The benchmark Stoxx Europe 600 Index gained 0.3 percent to
260.5 at 8:56 a.m. in London. Futures on the Standard & Poor’s
500 Index advanced 0.4 percent, while the MSCI Asia Pacific
Index also climbed 0.4 percent.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
David Merritt at 
